### English Title:
Egyptian Authorities Implement Strict Measures Against Food and Sweet Shops

### English Text Summary:
Egyptian authorities have taken stringent measures, including closures, against several food and sweet shops as part of a campaign to ensure food safety and consumer health. The closures affected well-known establishments, including "Belben," which faced public backlash after reports of food poisoning linked to its products. The National Food Safety Authority reported the presence of harmful bacteria and prohibited colors in various food items. Despite the company's claims that the closures were due to administrative reasons and not health complaints, the situation escalated following complaints from citizens. The closures have raised concerns about the impact on over 25,000 employees and the broader economy.

